verses.text: Let God arise , let his enemies be scattered : let them also that hate him flee before him.\f + \fr 68.1 \ft before…: Heb. from his face\f* \q1
As smoke is driven away , \add so\add* drive \add them\add* away : as wax melteth before the fire , \add so\add* let the wicked perish at the presence of God. \q1
But let the righteous be glad ; let them rejoice before God : yea, let them exceedingly rejoice.\f + \fr 68.3 \ft exceedingly…: Heb. rejoice with gladness\f* \q1
Sing unto God , sing praises to his name : extol him that rideth upon the heavens by his name \nd \+w Jah|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd*, and rejoice before him. \q1
A father of the fatherless , and a judge of the widows , \add is\add* God in his holy habitation. \q1
God setteth the solitary in families : he bringeth out those which are bound with chains : but the rebellious dwell in a dry \add land\add*.\f + \fr 68.6 \ft in families: Heb. in a house\f* \b \q1
O God , when thou wentest forth before thy people , when thou didst march through the wilderness ; Selah : \q1
The earth shook , the heavens also dropped at the presence of God : \add even\add* Sinai itself \add was moved\add* at the presence of God , the God of Israel. \q1
Thou, O God , didst send a plentiful rain , whereby thou didst confirm thine inheritance , when it was weary.\f + \fr 68.9 \ft send: Heb. shake out\f*\f + \fr 68.9 \ft confirm: Heb. confirm it\f* \q1
Thy congregation hath dwelt therein: thou, O God , hast prepared of thy goodness for the poor. \q1
The Lord gave the word : great \add was\add* the company of those that published \add it\add*.\f + \fr 68.11 \ft company: Heb. army\f* \q1
Kings of armies did flee apace : and she that tarried at home divided the spoil.\f + \fr 68.12 \ft did…: Heb. did flee, did flee\f* \q1
Though ye have lien among the pots , \add yet shall ye be as\add* the wings of a dove covered with silver , and her feathers with yellow gold. \q1
When the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was \add white\add* as snow in Salmon.\f + \fr 68.14 \ft in it…: or, for her, she\f* \b \q1
The hill of God \add is as\add* the hill of Bashan ; an high hill \add as\add* the hill of Bashan. \q1
Why leap ye, ye high hills ? \add this is\add* the hill \add which\add* God desireth to dwell in ; yea, the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* will dwell \add in it\add* for ever. \q1

The chariots of God \add are\add* twenty thousand , \add even\add* thousands of angels : the Lord \add is\add* among them, \add as in\add* Sinai , in the holy \add place\add*.\f + \fr 68.17 \ft even…: or, even many thousands\f* \q1

Thou hast ascended on high , thou hast led captivity captive : thou hast received gifts for men ; yea, \add for\add* the rebellious also, that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd* God might dwell \add among them\add*.\f + \fr 68.18 \ft for men: Heb. in the man\f* \q1
Blessed \add be\add* the Lord , \add who\add* daily loadeth us \add with benefits, even\add* the God of our salvation. Selah. \q1
\add He that is\add* our God \add is\add* the God of salvation ; and unto \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd* the Lord \add belong\add* the issues from death. \q1
But God shall wound the head of his enemies , \add and\add* the hairy scalp of such an one as goeth on still in his trespasses. \b \q1
The Lord said , I will bring again from Bashan , I will bring \add my people\add* again from the depths of the sea : \q1
That thy foot may be dipped in the blood of \add thine\add* enemies , \add and\add* the tongue of thy dogs in the same.\f + \fr 68.23 \ft dipped: or, red\f* \q1
They have seen thy goings , O God ; \add even\add* the goings of my God , my King , in the sanctuary. \q1
The singers went before , the players on instruments \add followed\add* after ; among \add them were\add* the damsels playing with timbrels. \q1
Bless ye God in the congregations , \add even\add* the Lord , from the fountain of Israel.\f + \fr 68.26 \ft from…: or, ye that are of the fountain of Israel\f* \q1

There \add is\add* little Benjamin \add with\add* their ruler , the princes of Judah \add and\add* their council , the princes of Zebulun , \add and\add* the princes of Naphtali.\f + \fr 68.27 \ft and their…: or, with their company\f* \q1
Thy God hath commanded thy strength : strengthen , O God , that which thou hast wrought for us. \q1
Because of thy temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto thee. \q1

Rebuke the company of spearmen , the multitude of the bulls , with the calves of the people , \add till every one\add* submit himself with pieces of silver : scatter thou the people \add that\add* delight in war.\f + \fr 68.30 \ft the company…: or, the beasts of the reeds\f*\f + \fr 68.30 \ft scatter…: or, he scattereth\f* \q1
Princes shall come out of Egypt ; Ethiopia shall soon stretch out her hands unto God. \b \q1
Sing unto God , ye kingdoms of the earth ; O sing praises unto the Lord ; Selah : \q1
To him that rideth upon the heavens of heavens , \add which were\add* of old ; lo, he doth send out his voice , \add and that\add* a mighty voice.\f + \fr 68.33 \ft send…: Heb. give\f* \q1
Ascribe ye strength unto God : his excellency \add is\add* over Israel , and his strength \add is\add* in the clouds.\f + \fr 68.34 \ft clouds: or, heavens\f* \q1
O God , \add thou art\add* terrible out of thy holy places : the God of Israel \add is\add* he that giveth strength and power unto \add his\add* people. Blessed \add be\add* God.
